@dmalan we should probably publish to PyPI on tags rather than commits to master? This will give us a little more control over when to release a new version, and won't require us to bump the version number for every small tweak that's merged into master.

Alternatively, we may create a `production` branch or such, and only merge to that when a new version is ready to be deployed, having Travis deploy on commits to `production` instead.

